text:
Chat is misinformed regarding 'kcal'; do not listen to them.

This confusion is because Americans not using/liking/understanding metric.
In the metric system, 'calorie' (small calorie, lowercase) is the amount of energy required to heat 1 gram of water by 1¬∞C, whereas a 'kcal/Calorie' (large calorie, uppercase) is the amount of energy required to heat 1kg of water by 1¬∞C, and is equivalent to 1,000 small calories, hence the 'kilo'.

Whenever you see 'calorie' (regardless if it's capitalized or not) in reference to nutrition and fitness, it's always the large calorie, which is an equivalent amount of energy as a kilocalorie/kcal.
So, you're sort of accidentally correct calling it '25 calories', since we all know you're referring to the large Calorie (i.e. that used in nutrition and fitness), and the small calorie is pretty much only used in applied physics and chemistry.

If all of that is confusing, just keep in mind that the number you see in the game is the kilograms of water that can be heated by 1¬∞C with the energy you expended.
----
EDIT: 1kg = 2.2 lbs, and 1L of water = 1kg

EDIT #2: Chat should also be informed that's holly; mistletoe has white berries.
